        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 22 at 7:02PM CDT until June 22 at 8:00PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Western Oldham County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Northwestern Deaf Smith County in the Panhandle of Texas...
South central Dallam County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Hartley County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 800 PM CDT.

* At 701 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 10 miles east of Amistad to 11 miles southeast of
Nara Visa to 9 miles northwest of Glenrio, moving northeast at 35
mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
Hail damage to vehicles is expected.

* Locations impacted include...
Dalhart, Glenrio, Ware, and Romero.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with these storms, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
